        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 6:33PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 633 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hanging Rock State Park, or near Danbury, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danbury...
Francisco...
Collinstown...
Hanging Rock State Park...
Capella...
Pinnacle...
and Vade Mecum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
